Variable = a resuable container for a value
Primitive = simple value stored directly in memory (stack)
Reference = memory address (stack) that points to the (heap)


Primitive vs Reference
--------------------------------
int   	    String
double   	  array
char   	    object
boolean


⭐ Beginner Level

- Login + Registration System
- Online Book Store
- Simple Inventory App
- Student Management System

⭐ Intermediate Level

  - E-commerce Backend
  - Parcel Delivery Backend (আপনার প্রজেক্টের মতো)  
  - Hospital Management System  
  - Banking Transaction Simulation

⭐ Advanced Level (CV তে দিলে অনেক শক্তিশালী)
  - Microservices-based E-commerce
 - Restaurant POS (billing, products, orders)
 - Online Payment Service (Bkash/Nagad-like simulation)
 - Vehicle Tracking System
 - Hotel Booking System
 - ERP System (Inventory + HR + Sales)
